name: Anne Bet
text: NEVER EVER GET GAS HERE. They upcharge the gas! What's the most important part of a gas station? The &#@!ing gas. I pulled in because the price was lower than all of the other stations. But only on the sign. I started pumping and things weren't adding up. I literally got out a calculator and my final price was 11 cents more per gallon than what the sign and the pump showed, which means the pumps are broken...or rigged. The cashier didn't know what to do so I had to walk away knowing that I over paid. I guess the BBB will sort this out.

name: Ben H
text: This used to be a pretty decent fuel station with a pretty good deli. But since it has changed owners and turned into some kind of hybrid circle k, BP, whatever it is, this place has just gotten rundown and just plain gross. The deli, the actual store, the restrooms, everything. At 6:30 A.M., the coffee bar was out of everything but decaf, the creamer machines are out of service, and the whole thing looked like kindergartners had played in it! If this is in fact a Circle K, it is one of the sorriest ones I have ever been in. If you can just hold it for one more exit, I would highly recommend passing this place on by.

name: Thomas Earp
text: Prepaid for $20 on diesel in an F250 while helping our daughter move and they held $300 for about a week. The bank shut off our card because of suspected fraudulent activity immediately. Called to find out what happened, everyone was very rude and less than helpful. We had to wait for new cards to be mailed out. We haven't been back since, there are plenty of much better choices in the area, and we have told all of our friends to be very cautious. Terrible, terrible  choice to do business here. It was much better prior to changing from BP. I just feel sorry for people traveling that don't know better.

name: Sean Tankersley
text: I paid $6 for a small chocolate coffee shake and it tasted like a workout drink. Definitely water based with no milk. It tasted absolutely nothing like coffee at all and was very bland. Save your money and get Arby's.

resp.text:
Hi Sean. We agree - Arby's has a great shake.

And, you're correct! We do not have dairy-based protein smoothies; we have coconut milk sweetened with Stevia as "magic milk" base.  We use Ghirardelli chocolate powder & Ghirardelli syrup. Our mocha powder has 20g protein/scoop.

We certainly would have made you another option (probably recommending no protein powder). Hopefully there's something else you'd like to try - maybe a delicious pop? Our Cold Brew is a popular coffee-flavored pop. Next time you're downtown,  please introduce yourself to Pop Guy!

Thanks for taking time to provide your feedback. We value your opinion 🙂
